<title>UK: Telspec slides into loss, passes dividend.</title>
<headline>Telspec slides into loss, passes dividend.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-09-11</dateline>
<text>
<p>Six months to June 30 1996</p>
<p>			   (million stg unless stated)</p>
<p> Shr (pence)		13.75 loss	   vs 8.99 earnings</p>
<p> Dividend (pence)	 nil		    vs 1.8</p>
<p> Pretax		     6.0 loss	     vs 4.3 profit</p>
<p> Turnover		   35.0		   vs 27.9</p>
<p>NOTE - Telecommunications equipment manufacturer Telspec Plc said a less favourable product mix, difficulties with materials purchasing and disappointing order volumes in Australia and Middle East were to blame for the loss.  </p>
<p> Operating result	 5.87 loss	    vs 4.38 profit</p>
<p> Interest payable	 0.33		   vs 0.12</p>
<p> Tax UK		     1.68 credit	  vs 0.61 charge</p>
<p> Net taxed		  4.37 loss	    vs 2.92 profit</p>
<p> Attributable	     4.36 loss	    vs 2.85 profit</p>
<p>The company said it expects to return to profitable trading in the second half of the year.</p>
<p>-- London Newsroom +44 171 542 7717</p>
